<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-06-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-06-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="428" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d428">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Takahira</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-06-23"><hi rend="italic">June 23,
                                1904</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 152.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your note, No. 37, of the 23d
                            ultimo, I have the honor to inform you that the Department is in receipt
                            of a telegram, dated the 22d instant, from the United States ambassador
                            at St. Petersburg, reporting that the viceroy declines, for
                            considerations pertaining to the state of war, to grant the request of
                            your Government that the crew of the <hi rend="italic">Hagino-ura
                                Maru</hi> be returned to Japan.</p>
                        <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>